Adding this place to the list of must-repeats.

Can’t wait to go back!

San Francisco was a dream, but @tajcampton made it unforgettable. Thoughtful service, cozy rooms, and mornings that started with slow coffee and soft light. From the room to the people, every detail felt personal. This set the perfect tone to explore the city!

Here are some must do’s in San Francisco:

1. Walk/bike along the Golden Gate Bridge 

2. Fisherman’s Wharf - try clam chowder and watch sea lions at Pier 39

3. Ride a cable car - a must when you’re in San Francisco 

4. Lombard street - walk down the “crookedest street in the world”

5. Sausalito - take a ferry to Sausalito and spend a day at this coastal town

6. Ghirardelli Square - try chocolate samples and grab an ice cream sundae
